Messages: 110 is the age a person must attain in order to be considered a supercentenarian.
110 is the number of stories (by common reckoning) of the Sears Tower in Chicago.
110 is the TCP port used for POP3 email protocol.
110 is a card game related to Forty-five (card game).
110 is a common name for mains electricity in North America, despite the nominal voltage actually being 120V (range 110-120).
110 is the atomic number of darmstadtium.
110 is a percentage in the expression "To give 110%", meaning to give a little more effort than one's maximum effort.

110 is the number also known as "eleventy", a term made famous by linguist and author J. R. R. Tolkien (Bilbo Baggins celebrates his eleventy-first birthday at the beginning of The Lord of the Rings) and derived from the Old English hund endleofantig.
110 is the number of stories of both towers of the former World Trade Center in New York.
